-- Germany's TAG sells commercial real estate business to Apollo
-- By Maria Sheahan
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 02:08PM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, March 28 (Reuters) - Germany's TAG Immobilien <TEGG.DE> agreed to sell the bulk of its commercial real estate business to Apollo Global Management <APO.N> in a deal worth 297 million euros ($408 million) as it seeks to focus on residential properties.

Apollo European Principal Finance Fund II, a fund affiliated with Apollo, will pay about 130 million euros in cash and assume loans worth 167 million, TAG said on Friday. TAG said it expected to generate a small book profit from the deal, which is due to close in the second quarter. It said it was keeping a 20 percent stake in the business, called TAG Gewerbeimmobilien.